    • Constructor Detail

      • BASS_MIDI_EVENT

        public BASS_MIDI_EVENT()
        Create an object that holds a null BASS_MIDI_EVENT.
        The call isNull() on the object created will returns true.
          BASS_MIDI_EVENT obj = new BASS_MIDI_EVENT();
  (obj == null) <=> false
  obj.isNull() <=> true
        To creates a new BASS_MIDI_EVENT, use the static "constructor" : 
          BASS_MIDI_EVENT obj = BASS_MIDI_EVENT.allocate();
        See Also:
        allocate()

    • Method Detail

      • asBASS_MIDI_EVENT

        public static BASS_MIDI_EVENT asBASS_MIDI_EVENT(Pointer pointer)
        Create a view of the Pointer object as a BASS_MIDI_EVENT object.
        This view is valid only if the memory holded by the Pointer holds a BASS_MIDI_EVENT object.

      • allocate

        public static BASS_MIDI_EVENT allocate()
        Allocate a new BASS_MIDI_EVENT.
        The call isNull() on the object created will return false.
          BASS_MIDI_EVENT obj = BASS_MIDI_EVENT.allocate();
  (obj == null) <=> obj.isNull() <=> false
